dfischer.utils

Class LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField

  • public class LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField
extends java.lang.Object
    Allows to define fixed (predefined) "User Input Fields" for load test plug-in input configuration data.

    Notice: an "User Input Fields" is a load test program option which must be set before a test-run can be started.

    See Also:
    LoadtestPluginInterface

    • Constructor Detail

      • LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField

        public LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField(java.lang.String varName,
                                 boolean incrementVarName,
                                 java.lang.String defaultValue)
        Creates a new definition for a fixed user input field.

        Notice: the label text of a user input field is defined by the method GenericPluginInterface.getInputParameterLabels().

        Parameters:
        varName - the variable name of the user input field
        incrementVarName - if true, increments the variable name if an other variable already exists with the same name: Example: "varname", "varname_2", "varname_3" ...
        defaultValue - the default value of the user input field
        See Also:
        GenericPluginInterface.getInputParameterLabels()
